<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  tinyxml.vcxproj : x64 from-source StaticLibrary build of tinyxml (Phase 33,
  X64-01). tinyxml is the ONE third-party dep with NO Restoration x64 DLL
  fallback (it ships as a static lib, never a DLL), so the x64 build MUST be
  from source. Authored from the four tinyxml .cpp (the test xmltest.cpp is
  excluded), mirroring the sharedMath StaticLibrary shape.

  OUTPUT-NAME CONTRACT (reviews fix #5, VERIFIED against SwgClient.vcxproj:103
  + :216 AdditionalDependencies): SwgClient links BOTH `tinyxmld.lib` and
  `tinyxmld_STL.lib` (the `d` debug suffix is used in BOTH Debug AND Release
  link lines in the shipped tree). The `_STL` flavor is the TIXML_USE_STL build.
  This project builds the STL flavor as $(OutDir)tinyxmld_STL.lib and copies it
  to tinyxmld.lib in a post-build step so BOTH names that SwgClient lists resolve
  at Plan 05's link (a bare `tinyxml.lib` output would LNK1181/2019). No
  SwgClient-closure source actually #includes tinyxml's STL API, so emitting one
  build under both names is correct; the legacy two-.dsp split (tinyxml_lib.dsp
  non-STL + tinyxmlSTL.dsp STL) collapses to one x64 project for swg.sln.

  MACRO NAME (corrected vs the plan text): tinyxml's STL switch is `TIXML_USE_STL`
  (tinyxml.h:46), NOT `TINYXML_USE_STL`. Defining the wrong token leaves the STL
  std::string overloads out -> the `_STL` flavor would be identical to non-STL.

  OutDir DEPTH (reviews fix #5): from this file at
  src/external/3rd/library/tinyxml/build/win32/ it is SEVEN `..\` up to the repo
  root (win32->build->tinyxml->library->3rd->external->src->root), then
  src\compile\win32\tinyxml\x64\$(Configuration)\ (the \x64\ isolation). Peers
  disagree on depth (udplibrary=4, dpvs=6); this was counted + filesystem-verified,
  NOT assumed 5.

  Imports x64-platform.props (also 7 `..\` up, under src\build\win32\) for the
  shared x64 ClCompile block (warnings/std/RTTI/EH + the N1 /we4311/4312 guardrail).
  Headers live in ..\..\include\ (tinyxml.h / tinystr.h); the 4 .cpp are in ..\..\src\.
-->
<Project DefaultTargets="Build" ToolsVersion="12.0" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/msbuild/2003">
